membership has its privileges the impact of gatt on international trade siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display membership has its privileges the impact of gatt on international trade type scid working paper 250 author s judith goldstein douglas rivers michael tomz published 08 1 05 region general download pdf abstract recent research concludes that membership in the gatt wto had no effect on foreign trade by mistakenly classifying many countries as outsiders even though they had rights and obligations under the agreement this work systematically underestimates the effect of gatt we correct the downward bias in previous estimates our analyses show that gatt substantially increased trade and that its effects were relatively stable across countries and over time stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
